coriander seed, and the colour thereof as the colour of bdellium.","year":-1490},{"id":"recQ7UY5E9leXNOZD","ref":"Num.11.8","text":"And the people went about, and gathered it, and ground it in mills, or beat it in a mortar, and baked it in pans, and made cakes of it: and the taste of it was as the taste of fresh oil.","year":-1490}]}
